snippet.textDisplay:
I don't go on them anymore, but the worst one I ever went on was the old wooden Crazy Mouse in Blackpool (NOT the one on the pier, the other one).
It was my first (and last) time on it, but my Mum knew all about it. She lay down in the cart and made me lay on her (as far back as we could) with her arms squeezing me tightly. Everyone else was sitting normal..... I do not know how they did that.
It was not smooth at all. Really rickety, it's like you could feel each wooden slot it went over. And it jerked at every corner ( when I say it jerked, I mean IT JERKED ), I honestly thought the cart was going to fly clean off (which was so scary)! My pre-teen neck, shoulders, and back were fucked the rest of the holiday and after we got back home.
It also managed to pull one of my Mum's little hoop earrings out. She realised right after, and we quickly went back and luckily the worker pulled it from our cart.
I was just relieved we came off it alive.
'Crazy' indeed.

It was not smooth at all.  Really rickety,  it's like you could feel each wooden slot it went over.  And it jerked at every corner ( when I say it jerked, I mean *IT JERKED* ),  I honestly thought the cart was going to fly clean off (which was *so* scary)!  My pre-teen neck, shoulders, and back were fucked the rest of the holiday  and after we got back home. 
It also managed to pull one of my Mum's little hoop earrings out.  She realised right after,  and we quickly went back  and luckily the worker pulled it from our cart. 
I was just relieved we came off it alive. 
'Crazy' indeed.
